parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and in extreme cases, engine fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
smoke coming from the hood
oil leaking onto the manifold
engine explosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut down of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling
shut down
loss of power
failure to restart
warning lights flashing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause erratic behavior of gauges, warning lights, and other systems, which can lead to confusion, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Gauges malfunctioning
warning lights flashing
speedometer reading incorrectly
DIC malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause rough idle, loss of power, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rough idle
loss of power
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Instrument panel lights and headlights turn off and on
seat control button plastic piece fractures
door locks become inoperable
horn operation is faulty
and computer malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks can cause the driver and passengers to be trapped inside the vehicle, leading to safety risks in emergency situations.
symptoms: Door locks become inoperable
unable to open door from inside with manual controls
unable to unlock door with remote
and unable to open door with key from outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking capability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Battery acid leaking onto brake lines
loss of braking capability
and failure to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the computer system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Computer malfunctions
vehicle shuts off while driving
and engine racing out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blinker system can cause accidents due to lack of visibility and communication with other drivers.
symptoms: Right-side blinkers stopped working
front and back blinkers do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration and loss of brake function can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the driver may lose control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the brake pedal feels like it's stuck or non-responsive
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the driver may experience a sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
and the driver may experience a sudden loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise and vibration in the steering system can cause driver fatigue, distraction, and loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates or makes a noise
the driver experiences a "stick-slip" feeling while turning
and the vehicle may be difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic system can cause a loss of braking and steering function, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of braking and steering ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The engine catches on fire
there is a popping noise from the engine
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent locking of the steering wheel and column can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel and column lock up intermittently
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to inadequate protection of occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not extend or retract
the buckle is stuck
the seat belt is too short
the seat belt has too much slack
the seat belt does not lock or unlock
the seat belt does not release from the retractor.
